# Upfluence Influencer Pulse — Project Documentation

## 1. Project Architecture Overview

The application is architected as an edge-ready, full-stack single-page application (SPA) with server-side computational capabilities. It uses a split backend/frontend structure optimized to mitigate client-side leaks of private API keys and avoid unnecessary network overhead:

* **Server-Side Layer (`upfluence.server.ts` & `upfluence.functions.ts`):** Handles secure client-credential OAuth token exchange and structures raw downstream queries to the Upfluence API. It features an isolated in-memory cache mechanism with a 15-minute Time-To-Live (TTL) window to throttle repetitive API executions and preserve platform performance.
* **Data Transport Layer:** Powered by TanStack Start's `createServerFn`, providing fully typesafe JSON transport handshakes between server-side analytics filters and client UI widgets.
* **Client-Side UI Layer (`index.tsx`):** Implements an un-hydrated, hyper-reactive dashboard powered by TanStack Query for frontend asynchronous state lifecycle management. Client metrics automatically adjust on the fly through an algorithmic weight matrix.

